[When Anne Volokh and her family immigrated to the U.S. 14 years
ago,]1 [they started life in Los Angeles with only $400.]2 [They'd
actually left the Soviet Union with $480,]3 [but during a stop in
Italy Ms. Volokh dropped $80 on a black velvet suit.]4 [Not
surprisingly, she quickly adapted to the American way.]5 [Three months
after she arrived in L.A.]6 [she spent $120]7 [she didn't have]8 [for
a hat.]9 [("A turban,"]10 [she specifies,]11 ["though it wasn't the
time for that 14 years ago.]12 [But I loved turbans.")]13

[Since then she has become wealthy.]14 [Her husband and older son]15
[-- a computer prodigy]16 [profiled in The Wall Street Journal in
1981,]17 [when he was 13 --]18 [run a software company with expected
sales this year of $10 million.]19 [Most recently, she has become the
publisher of Movieline, a four-year-old Los Angeles magazine]20 [that
began national distribution last month, with an initial press run of
100,000 copies.]21 [Distributed by the Hearst Corp. 's Eastern
News,]22 [the glossy publication melds Vanity Fair's gossipy archness
and Premiere's earnest delving into behind-the-scenes minutiae, with a
special emphasis on Tinseltown as fashion trendsetter.]23 [It's being
sold through bookstores, newsstands and some video stores.]24

[Though Ms. Volokh is a small woman,]25 [she has an outsized
personality and dramatic flair]26 [that seem perfectly suited to
capitalism]27 [as it is practiced in Hollywood.]28 [Certainly life for
her has changed considerably since the days in Kiev,]29 [when she
lived with her parents, her husband and her two sons in a 2 1/2-room
apartment]30 [in what she calls "silent internal immigration,"]31
[dreaming of escape.]32

[Now, for example, she owns 48 hats.]33 [However, she remembers the
lean years]34 [and recalls with relish wearing her first major
American purchase]35 [-- that turban --]36 [10 years later and having
a Los Angeles boutique owner ask her]37 [if it was a Chanel.]38 [With
obvious satisfaction, she says]39 [she told him:]40 ["No darling, I
just give it a Chanel look."]41 [She keeps track of the rest of her
hats]42 [by stapling Polaroid snapshots to the outside of each
